text:
Wealthy Americans' homes generate around 25% more greenhouse gases compared to lower-income residences, mostly due to larger size, a new study finds.

In some particularly affluent US suburbs, emissions are up to 15 times higher than nearby neighborhoods. https://t.co/41tUCOSojB
